<hr />
<h1>Dont miss: '<em>Gramophone</em> Presents... Mozart'</h1>
<p><a href="https://www.magsubscriptions.com/mozart"><img style="width: 100%; height: 100%;" src="/media/229427/0001484_gramophone-presents-mozart_550.png?width=100%;height=100%" alt="" data-udi="umb://media/ee4a5c07999546ee820f818cc1a02e3a" /></a></p>
<p>Wolfgang Amadeus Mozart collectors' edition of <em>Gramophone</em>, 99 years in the making. <em>Gramophone</em>'s expert writers celebrate arguably the most naturally gifted musician in history, one whose masterpieces across the breadth of musical genres, from choral and opera, to symphonies and sonatas, are among the most beloved &ndash; and most played &ndash; of all works today. In these 100 pages we bring together authoritative articles from the magazine's 99 year archive including:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Reviews of iconic recordings</strong></li>
<li><strong>Interviews with some of today's leading interpreters</strong></li>
